{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-01637/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-01637"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:16:37"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A woman eats from a spoon while smiling at a man sitting opposite her."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-01637","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-01637"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1/8eb19d29-4c6d-401a-b7e8-07cc3c043b9f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T14:39:58.045Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma’s red dress, of course, is a far cry from the couture clothes she’ll wear throughout the rest of the film. It also resembles the waitress dress that she wears when the characters meet. Nonetheless, its vibrant color, also unlike the muted colors that Reynolds will dress her in, symbolizes the energy and dynamism that she’ll bring into Reynolds’s life.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:805.3930131004367,463.0240174672488,621.866812227074,605.1200873362445"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1/32d1a2ea-08b4-4b5f-9393-f1bb9df395d1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T14:40:10.745Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma’s side of the frame also includes a large lamp and the lamp on their table has a red lampshade—she is connected to sources of light as she will soon become the light of his life (or as Barry Egan would put it in <em>Punch-Drunk Love</em>, the love in his life). Alma is also right in front of a window—<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW23623897 BCX0\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-01537.html\"><u>much like in their initial encounter,</u></a> this framing suggests that she will break open Reynolds’ life and the unusual predilection the film reveals in its final plot point.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01637/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1567.6200873362445,598.5698689956332,346.94323144104806,369.37772925764193"}}}]}]}]}